  "prompt": "Do Apple employees get discounts?",
  "response": "Yes, Apple employees do receive discounts on Apple products as part of their employee benefits. While the exact details of the discount program are not publicly disclosed, it is known that employees are eligible for significant savings on Apple products, including iPhones, Macs, iPads, and accessories. These discounts are typically available for personal use and may have limits on the number of products that can be purchased at a discount within a certain time period.\n\nIn addition to product discounts, Apple employees often receive other benefits such as health insurance, retirement plans, stock purchase options, employee stock ownership plans (ESOPs), wellness programs, and more. The company is known for offering competitive benefits to attract and retain talent.\n\nIt's important to note that the specifics of the employee discount program and other benefits can vary based on the employee's position, location, and length of service with the company. Additionally, some benefits may be subject to change over time as the company revises its policies.",
